=Xingshi yinyuan zhuan 醒世姻緣傳 Awakening the World=
==Editions==
* 西周生: 醒世姻緣傳. Shanghai: Guji, 1981 (repr. 1985)
==Literature==
===PhD Dissertations===
* Yenna Wu: Marriage Destinies to Awaken the World: A literary study of Xingshi yinyuan zhuan. Harvard University, 1986
* [[Daria Berg]]: The Xingshi yinyuan zhuan: A Study of Utopia and the Perception of the World in Seventeenth-Century Chinese Discourse. University of Oxford, 1994
* Xiaoyi Liu: Clothing, Food and Travel: Ming Material Culture as reflected in Xingshi yinyuan zhuan. University of Arizona, 2010
===Monographs===
* Yenna Wu: Ameliorative Satire and the Seventeenth-Century Chinese Novel Xingshi yinyuan zhuan: Marriage as Retribution, Awakening the World. Lampeter: Edwin Mellen, 1999
* [[Daria Berg]]: Carnival in China: A Reading of the Xingshi yinyuan zhuan. Leiden: Brill, 2002
